<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-07T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-07T10:00:00-05:00" n="711" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d711">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.21112 RP/8–745: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-07T10:00:00-05:00">August 7,
                                    1945—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 4:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1048. Emtel 1041, Aug. 4.<note n="55" xml:id="d711fn55">Not
                                printed.</note> Minister of Finance, Santamaria, has just confirmed
                            to the Embassy that an executive resolution has been signed by the
                            Minister of Foreign Affairs and President López ordering liquidation of
                            Axis spearhead firms.</p>
                        <p>Minister Santamaria expressed confidence that no further obstacles would
                            remain in the way of prompt liquidation of Axis firms. Text of
                            resolution follows in Embtel 1049.<note n="56" xml:id="d711fn56">August
                                7, 11 a.m., not printed.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wiley</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>